Let $\angle A = x$. Since \angle{AB} and \angle{CD} are corresponding angles between parallel lines, we have \angle{B} = \angle{AB} = x. Since \angle{D} = 2\angle{B}, we have \angle{D} = 2x. The sum of the internal angles of a triangle is 180^\circ. Thus, we can say that
\begin{align*}180^\circ &= \angle{A} + \angle{B} + \angle{D} \mid /- (x + 2x)\\2x &= 180^\circ - 3x \rightarrow 5x = 180^\circ \rightarrow x = 36^\circ\end{align*}\\Since
\begin{align*}m\angle A &= x\\m\angle D &= 2x\\m\angle A &= x\\AC &= \angle D\ because\ corresponding\ angles\ are\ equal\\&=\ 2x\end{align*}
From similar triangles $DAB$ and $ACD$, we have
\begin{align*}\left( \dfrac{AB}{\bf DC}\right)^2 &= \left( \dfrac{AD}{\bf AC}\right)^{\!2}\\(AB)/b &= (a)/2x\\AB &= (a)/2x\cdot\ \ \, b\\&=\ 2a-b\end{align*}
